# Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the scAId project.

## Changes Made

### Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 via npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` to lock dependency versions

### Code Integration
Modified both main JavaScript entry points to integrate Speed Insights:

**js/landing.js** (Landing Page):
- Added import: `import { injectSpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights';`
- Called `injectSpeedInsights()` after analytics injection

**js/render.js** (Editor Page):
- Added import: `import { injectSpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights';`
- Called `injectSpeedInsights()` after analytics injection

## Implementation Details

- **Framework**: Vite (vanilla JavaScript)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Approach**: Used the vanilla JavaScript integration method from official Vercel documentation
- **Function Used**: `injectSpeedInsights()` - automatically injects the Speed Insights tracking script

This follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Vite projects. The implementation mirrors the existing Vercel Analytics pattern already in use in the project.

## Testing

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ All dependencies installed correctly
- ✅ No linting errors (project has no linter configured)
- ✅ Speed Insights will activate automatically when deployed to Vercel

## Next Steps

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Speed Insights will automatically begin collecting real user performance metrics
3. View metrics in the Vercel dashboard under Speed Insights section
